Example
End the loop when
i
is equal to 4:
for (int i = 0; i < 10; i++) {
  if (i == 4) {
    break;
  }
  System.out.println(i);
}

Definition and Usage
The
break
keyword is used to break out a
for
loop, a
while
loop or a
switch
block.
More Examples
Example
Break out of a while loop:
int i = 0;
while (i < 10) {
  System.out.println(i);
  i++;
  if (i == 4) {
    break;
  }
}

